```suggestion
  (hf'.yoneda_map_fst' _) â–¸ hf'.isPullback g
```

```suggestion
variable {Z : C} (i : Z âŸ¶ Y) (h : Z âŸ¶ X) (hi : yoneda.map i â‰« f' = yoneda.map h â‰« g)
```

```suggestion
* `Presheaf.representable` is a `MorphismProperty` expressing the fact that a morphism `f` of presheaves
  is representable, i.e. that any morphism from a representable presheaf to the target can be pulled back
  along `f` to a morphism from a representable presheaf to the source.
```
Feel free to rephrase, I just think there should be a short description here of what this means mathematically.
Good suggestion, I think I will spell it out a bit more even.

```suggestion
*  Whenever `f` is of type `yoneda.obj Y âŸ¶ G`, we also have `hf.fst' g : hf.pullback g âŸ¶ Y`
which is the preimage under `yoneda` of `hf.fst g`.
```

```suggestion
* `hom_ext`, `hom_ext'`, `lift`, `lift'` are variants of the universal property of
  `yoneda.obj (hf.pullback g)`, where as much as possible has been formulated internally to `C`.
```
Is there a reason for this blank line between bullet points? If not, could you remove it?
I think in my head these blank lines separated different categories somehow, but now that I look back on it I think that no blank line is better

```suggestion

@[reassoc (attr := simp)]
lemma lift_snd : hf.lift i h hi â‰« hf.snd g = h :=
```

I wonder if this should be generalized, i.e. let `Cáµ’áµ– â¥¤ Type v` just be any category, and `yoneda` just be any functor into it. The definition makes sense, and also a reasonable amount of the API below.
(And then have a specialized version for `yoneda`.)
`hasRelativePullbacks`, perhaps?
(I don't intend this comment to block merging, if it doesn't sounds like a good idea!)
I think this sound interesting / fun, so I will try it

One unfortunate part is that `FullyFaithful` is no longer an instance, so to use the `relativelyRepresentable` lemmas one would have to constantly supply the argument `Yoneda.fullyFaithful`. So to avoid this one would need a separate API for the case of presheaves anyways (so maybe lets merge this after all?).
Actually, maybe it's not so bad.
Done!

```suggestion
* We define `relativelyRepresentable` as a `MorphismProperty`. A morphism `f : X âŸ¶ Y` in `D` is
```

```suggestion
  said to be relatively representable with respect to `F` if for any `g : F.obj a âŸ¶ Y`, there exists a pullback square
```
